Determine the voltage gain of the common-source amplifier in Fig. $3.12 a$ with $V_{D D}=5 \mathrm{~V}$, $R_{D}=5 \mathrm{k} \Omega, k^{\prime}=\mu_{n} C_{o x}=100 \mu \mathrm{~A} / \mathrm{V}^{2}, W=50 \mu \mathrm{~m}, L=1 \mu \mathrm{~m}, V_{t}=0.8 \mathrm{~V}, L_{d}=0, X_{d}=0$, and $\lambda=0$. Assume the bias value of $V_{i}$ is 1 V.

