When \(r_{b}\) is non-negligible, its impact on transconductance and input resistance is significant at high current levels. For \(r_{b}>0\), assuming forward-active operation, the small-signal model in Fig. 3.18 applies. Here, the transconductance is:

$$
\begin{equation*}
